# Java + Maven Best Practices (.mdc)

**Scope:** Java applications and libraries built with Maven (multi-module or single-module).  
**Normative language:** MUST / SHOULD / MAY.

---

## 0) POM Structure & Organization

### General Principles
- Treat the POM as source code: small, reviewed, documented, versioned intentionally.
- Zero environment knowledge in POM: externalize via config files, env vars, or deployment tooling.

### Element Order
POM elements **MUST** be provided in this order:
1. `modelVersion`
2. `parent`
3. `groupId` / `artifactId` / `version` / `packaging`
4. `name` / `description` / `url`
5. `licenses` / `organization` / `developers` / `scm`
6. `properties`
7. `dependencyManagement`
8. `dependencies`
9. `repositories`
10. `build` (pluginManagement then plugins)
11. `reporting`
12. `profiles`

### Coordinates
**MUST** provide explicit `groupId`, `artifactId`, `version`, `name`, `description`, `url`:

```xml
<groupId>org.saltations.exemplar</groupId>
<artifactId>cli-exemplar</artifactId>
<packaging>jar</packaging>
<version>1.0.0</version>
<name>CLI Exemplar</name>
<description>Example CLI application</description>
<url>https://github.com/org/repo</url>
```

### Properties Naming Conventions
- Use `<properties>` to centralize JDK, dependency, and plugin versions.
- Use `<maven.compiler.release>21</maven.compiler.release>` to specify Java version (not `source`/`target`).
- Use `<project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>` to set the default encoding.
- **Dependency versions**: Use `artifact-name.version` naming (e.g., `<endeavour.version>0.3.0</endeavour.version>`).
- **Maven plugin versions**: Use `maven-[name]-plugin.version` naming (e.g., `<maven-jacoco-plugin.version>0.8.12</maven-jacoco-plugin.version>`).
- Append any other module-specific properties at the end of the properties list.

Example properties structure:
```xml
<properties>
  <!-- Java -->
  <maven.compiler.release>21</maven.compiler.release>
  <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>

  <!-- Dependency Versions (not already defined in parent pom.xml or parent bom) -->
  <endeavour.version>0.3.0</endeavour.version>

  <!-- Maven Plugins -->
  <maven-jacoco-plugin.version>0.8.12</maven-jacoco-plugin.version>
  <maven-release-plugin.version>3.0.1</maven-release-plugin.version>
  <maven-versions-plugin.version>2.17.1</maven-versions-plugin.version>
  <maven-enforcer-plugin.version>3.5.0</maven-enforcer-plugin.version>

  <!-- Module-specific plugin properties -->
  <enforcer.maven.min>3.9.0</enforcer.maven.min>
  <enforcer.java.min>21</enforcer.java.min>

  <!-- Module-specific -->
  <exec.mainClass>org.saltations.mn4.Mn4CliExemplarCommand</exec.mainClass>
</properties>
```

---

## 1) JDK & Build Reproducibility
- Projects **MUST** target an LTS JDK (17 or 21). Pin toolchains with `maven-toolchains-plugin`.
- `maven-compiler-plugin` **MUST** set `<release>` (not `source`/`target`).
- Reproducible builds **MUST** be enabled via `project.build.outputTimestamp` and deterministic jar options.
- Lock plugin versions in the parent POM’s `<pluginManagement>`.

## 2) Dependency Management
- Use a **single parent POM** with `<dependencyManagement>`; child modules **MUST NOT** pin versions for managed deps.
- Prefer vendor BOMs via `<type>pom</type><scope>import</scope>` (e.g., Spring, Jackson, Micrometer).
- Enable `maven-enforcer-plugin` to ban duplicate/conflicting deps, disallow snapshots in main, and require JDK/Maven ranges.
- Shade **only** for CLI fat-jars. Libraries **MUST NOT** shade runtime deps.

### Dependency Guidelines
- All dependencies **MUST** have a managed dependency declaration in `dependencyManagement` using the appropriate version property.
- All dependency usages **MUST** use the managed dependency declaration (no version specified in child modules).
- Keep dependencies lean: no unused libs, no duplicates, correct scopes (`compile`/`test`/`runtime`/`provided`).
- Avoid `system` scope; use normal dependencies or local repository.
- Avoid version ranges, `LATEST`, or `RELEASE`; pin exact versions via properties.

## 3) Testing & Coverage
- **MUST** separate unit vs integration tests: `surefire` (unit) and `failsafe` (IT, `*IT.java`) 
- Run ITs on CI; local opt-out via a profile flag.
- `jacoco` **SHOULD** enforce a project-wide minimum (e.g., INSTRUCTION ≥ 75%), with package-specific overrides when justified.

### Plugin Guidelines
- All plugins **MUST** have a managed plugin declaration in `pluginManagement` using the appropriate version property.
- Use minimal, purpose-driven plugins: `surefire`, `failsafe`, `jar`/`assembly`, `shade`, `jacoco`, `checkstyle`/`spotbugs`.
- Child modules **MUST NOT** specify plugin versions; inherit from parent `pluginManagement`.

### Profiles
- Use profiles **ONLY** for build variations (e.g., integration tests), not environment config.
- Environment-specific configuration **MUST** be externalized via config files, env vars, or deployment tooling.

## 4) Source Quality
- Enforce formatting with Spotless/Formatter (**SHOULD**). Style file lives in repo.
- Run `checkstyle`/`pmd`/`spotbugs` in `verify`; fail build on high severity only; warnings allowed but visible.
- No build-time logging; keep POM noise low.

## 5) Packaging & Modules
- Multi-module layout with a pure parent (`packaging` = `pom`); leaf modules are `jar`/`war` only.
- Avoid cyclic dependencies; enforce via Enforcer and/or ArchUnit.
- CLI apps: build one runnable JAR (assembly or shade). Libraries: plain JAR, no shaded transitive APIs.

## 6) Security & Supply Chain
- Use Enforcer banned-dependencies rules and/or OSS Index. Emit SBOM with `cyclonedx-maven-plugin` (**SHOULD**).
- Pin parent and plugin versions; no floating parents. No `systemPath` dependencies.

## 7) Versioning, Release, CI/CD
- Semantic versioning **SHOULD**. Releases via CI tags.
- `flatten-maven-plugin` for published POMs.
- CI caches `~/.m2` with checksums; use `--batch-mode` and a clean agent. Standard stage order: `validate → test → integration-test → verify → package → deploy`.

